:SelfTimer:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/snapshot.handbook
Snap Delay:
 
Choose the number of seconds Snapshot delays
before taking the picture. Counting starts
the moment you click to start the snap.

Between the time you start the snap and the 
time the snap is actually taken, you can pop up 
menus, move windows, and otherwise adjust the
screen for the picture.

Snap Delay is automatically set to 8 seconds if
you choose Hide Window During Capture.

:TimerBell:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/snapshot.handbook
Beep During Countdown

If you chose Snap Delay, you can choose to have
your workstation beep every second until the
snap is taken. 

:Hide:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/snapshot.handbook
Hide Snapshot During Capture

When Hide is chosen, all windows associated
with Snapshot disappear while the picture is
being taken. These include the base window, the
View window, and the Load/Save window. The
windows reappear after the snap.

When Hide is not chosen, the Snapshot windows
remain visible all the time.

Snap Delay is automatically set to 8 seconds if
you choose Hide Window During Capture. You
cannot change the timer in this case.

