:Appearance:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/snapshot.handbook
Scale to:

Actual Size  Prints the image actual size.
	     Printer image sizes might be a 
	     little different from screen image
	     sizes due to different resolutions.
	     Aspect ratio is always preserved.

Width	     Scales the image to the specified
	     width, preserving aspect ratio.

Height	     Scales the image to the specified
	     height, preserving aspect ratio.

Both	     Scales the image to the specified
	     width and height. Does not
	     preserve the original aspect ratio.

:Double:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/snapshot.handbook
Double Size:

Lets you double the size of the printed picture:

No	Prints the picture the same size as the 
	stored image.

Yes 	When the file is printed, doubles every
	bit in the image in both the x and y 
	dimensions--essentially doubling the 
	size of the image. Overrides other
	scaling options.

:Mono:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/snapshot.handbook
Monochrome Printer

Produces a monochrome raster file instead of a
colored one for faster printing on monochrome
printers.

